craterdog.collections.interfaces

Interface Indexed<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element managed by the collection.
    All Superinterfaces:
    craterdog.core.Composite, Iterable<E>, Iteratable<E>, craterdog.core.Sequential<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    List

    public interface Indexed<E>
extends Iteratable<E>
    This interface defines the methods that must be implemented by each collection that its elements to be manipulated based on their indexes. The indexing is unit based and allows positive indexes starting at the beginning of the collection or negative indexes starting at the end of the collection as follows: 
             1             2             3               N
    [element 1] . [element 2] . [element 3] ... [element N]
        -N          -(N-1)        -(N-2)            -1
    Author:
    Derk Norton
